                <h1>Unveiling the Genius: A Brief Biography of Leonardo da Vinci</h1>
                <p>Leonardo da Vinci, born on April 15, 1452, in Vinci, Italy, was a true polymath. Renowned as a painter, inventor, and scientist, his masterpieces like the "Mona Lisa" and "The Last Supper" revolutionized art. His curiosity spanned anatomy, engineering, and nature, marking him as a Renaissance visionary with unmatched creativity. Da Vinci passed away on May 2, 1519, leaving a lasting legacy.</p>
